<subSubSection pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="181" pageNumber="182">The type subspecies is characterised by the sessile, sometimes clasping, very acute, sometimes apiculate stem leaves and bracts, long slender inflorescence branches with flowers usually 2 -3 together, the sepals acute and the corolla 8-13 mm long. Spinescent side branches are few or absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
